I don’t like acrylic yarn for amigurumi but I believe it has perks. I usually only post the plushies I make from chenille or blanket yarn but I learned to crochet using acrylic. This allowed me to build a solid foundation and learn all the stitches and techniques I use today. 

Chenille yarn is notoriously difficult to work with, especially if you don’t have a lot of experience. It can be hard to see your stitches, make a magic ring, and difficult to sew pieces together (thank you shedding 😅). If you’re a beginner struggling with chenille yarn, I highly recommend learning the basics with acrylic first.

Acrylic yarn is not bad! Not only is it more affordable but it has a kind of charm you can’t get with chenille. The color options are nearly endless and some people even prefer it! There’s no right or wrong and it breaks my heart to see beginners get discouraged because they’re used to seeing chenille yarn. 

Don’t feel bad if your yarn is different, you can still make cute cuddly buddies! I know it’s hard, but don’t compare yourself to others. We all start somewhere. Be proud of what you make 💕

I’m looking for 6-9 crocheters to help me test my 3 in 1 forest buddies pattern! This is like a mix-and-match pattern. You can choose to give your buddy a shirt, a bow, a bag, or even leave him plain. I plan to design three different bags to correlate with each creature but I wanted to get this tester call posted to see who’s interested. 

Requirements:
🍄 Must be able to finish within 7 days of receiving the pattern (please only apply if you can finish on time)
🍄 Be able to provide me with honest feedback and final photos
🍄 Must be comfortable in a group chat with other crocheters
🍄 Post the finished plushie to your account and tag me
🍄 You can choose any colors you would like I only ask that you follow the base pattern

How to apply:
🐻 Have a public crochet account (so I can see your work)
🐻 Follow me, like, and save this post
🐻 Share the first slide of this post to your story
🐻 Comment which one you would like to test and tag 2-3 crocheters who may be interested (if you can’t decide just say so and I will pick one for you. You will still receive access to all three!)

Optional: Comment what type of yarn or colors you would use!

Thank you so much to everyone who applies and shares! Testers will be chosen on January 10-11th!

This custom order warmed my heart ❤️ The best gift you can give someone is full of love and this is the sweetest order I’ve had the opportunity to make!

These voice boxes add the perfect touch to a custom gift. If you live a long distance from family or spouses, or you want to keep a little piece of someone you love close, they’re perfect. You could even use it for the sound of a heartbeat 💗

The possibilities are endless and if you want something custom, I am more than happy to make the perfect plushie for you! It absolutely warms my heart to make such meaningful things for such wonderful people 🥹🫶

For those of you wondering why there’s a flap instead of it being crocheted in the body 🤔: 
A flap allows for it to be removable. This means if your plush needs a wash you can take it out and wash it. Also, if the batteries ever die this allows you to replace them so your recording can last for years to come!

It is worth noting if this is going to be a gift to a young child, buttons are a choking hazard and it’s better to have it crocheted into the body rather than a flap.
